Every name is is lovely in its own right, but pretty girl names are always in demand with their sweet sound and beautiful meanings. They’re all across the top of the charts, and it’s no surprise why. From French finds to Polynesian picks, we have the pretty girl names you’ve been looking for.

Many of today’s most popular picks are pretty girl names like Sophia and Isabella. Parents are loving on these gorgeous names, and their simpler friends Emma and Bella are also trending hard. Some other names are rising like Lola and Isla, two stunners we’re loving more and more. Pretty girl names will continue to rule the charts and will always be in style.

Long, frillier finds are plentiful among pretty girl names like Valentina and Penelope. These names are fit for a princess and would be adorable on any little girl. We especially love Arabella and Mirabelle for a splash of sweetness. At the same time, there are also petite pretty picks like Nia and Mila to explore. They’re just as lovely as their grander sisters, yet pack a wallop of adorable you can’t help but love.

Less common pretty girl names are still waiting out there for their time to shine as well. French names like Elodie and Lucille are simply stunning but not too popular. You can also look for variants of popular names like Lucy and Amelia with names like Lucia and Amalia. Transport yourself to the islands with Polynesian picks like Maleah and Alani, or head to Japan with Sakura and Amaya.

Pretty girl names come in all styles, and we love them all. From elaborate princess names to soft and sweet finds, we have the pretty girls you seek all in one place. Try out these pretty picks. You never know what beauty you’ll find next!
